  <h2>Learning Objectives</h2>
	<div class="yellowbox">
	 <p>
	  This course provides a foundation in web development and design through a comprehensive study and hands-on application of contemporary Hypertext Markup Language (HTML) and Cascading Style Sheets (CSS). The course is designed for the beginner and is a guide on how to build web sites effectively. Web standards are emphasized throughout the course as we move from a beginning level to students being able to construct their own designs with native code on a live server using industry driven standards and methodologies.</p>	 
	</div>
	<div class="details">
	Specific learning objectives for this course include:
		<ul style="list-style:square;margin-left:25px;">
			<li>explain and utilize web design and development standards,</li>
			<li>use proper design documentation in web site planning, </li>
			<li>effectively use a text-based editor writing markup,</li>
			<li>use contemporary HTML elements,</li>
			<li>use contemporary CSS application,</li>
			<li>build easy to use navigation structures,&nbsp; </li>
			<li>utilize data tables effectively, </li>
			<li>incorporate interactive forms into web pages,</li>
			<li>effectively use images on web sites,</li>
			<li>understand HTML and CSS trends,</li>
			<li>apply social media elements into a web site,</li>
			<li>prepare for effective design and layout development,</li>
			<li>manage a live web site, and</li>
			<li>effectively use search tools to find answers to development questions.</li>
		</ul>
	 </div>	
		
	 <div class="yellowbox">
	  <span class="stronger">Prerequisite Knowledge:</span> &nbsp;an overall understanding of the role and aspects of web design and development, basic computer operation, file management, and web application experience as a user.
